name: Task
description: File a unit of work — one issue per task, mirroring the ROADMAP checklist so the tracker can sync it.
labels: [task]
body:
  - type: markdown
    attributes:
      value: |
        Use this form to file a single, assignable task. One issue equals one unit of work, which keeps progress legible and lets a Project board, milestone, and assignee each track exactly one thing. Fields below mirror the engagement TODO schema in `ROADMAP.md`, so editing the checklist and re-running the tracker create-or-updates this issue rather than duplicating it. Pick from the dropdowns instead of typing free text — fixed options keep labels and Project fields consistent across the team and stay legible without relying on color.
  - type: input
    id: summary
    attributes:
      label: Summary
      description: One sentence stating the outcome this task delivers, written so a teammate who lacks your context can tell what "done" looks like.
      placeholder: Reconcile intake totals against the publisher's published figures.
    validations:
      required: true
  - type: textarea
    id: definition-of-done
    attributes:
      label: Definition of done
      description: The checklist that must be true to close this issue. Make each item observable so a reviewer can verify it, rather than restating the title.
      placeholder: |
        - [ ] Totals match the source within tolerance
        - [ ] Reconciliation step added to the pipeline
        - [ ] Result documented in decision-log.md
      value: |
        - [ ]
    validations:
      required: true
  - type: dropdown
    id: level
    attributes:
      label: Level
      description: The escalation level (L0-L5) this task belongs to, so it can be grouped under the matching milestone and Project field.
      options:
        - L0
        - L1
        - L2
        - L3
        - L4
        - L5
    validations:
      required: false
  - type: dropdown
    id: priority
    attributes:
      label: Priority
      description: How urgently this should be picked up, so the board can be sorted by what matters now rather than by guesswork.
      options:
        - High
        - Medium
        - Low
    validations:
      required: false
  - type: dropdown
    id: size
    attributes:
      label: Size
      description: A rough effort estimate (S/M/L) used for planning capacity, not a commitment — refine it as the work becomes clear.
      options:
        - S
        - M
        - L
    validations:
      required: false
  - type: dropdown
    id: blocking
    attributes:
      label: Blocking?
      description: Whether this task gates other work or a guarded action (for example ingesting sensitive data or publishing). Mark Yes so it can be modeled as a dependency and resolved before the gate.
      options:
        - "No"
        - "Yes"
    validations:
      required: false
  - type: input
    id: links
    attributes:
      label: Links
      description: References that ground the task — a roadmap row, a source dataset, a prior PR, or a decision-log entry — so a reviewer can follow the trail without asking.
      placeholder: ROADMAP.md row 3; data/raw/source.csv; decision-log.md 2026-06-17
    validations:
      required: false
